    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The \"case-by-case\" thing sounds okay in theory, but isn't it a bit of a slippery slope? Like, if we start making exceptions for one group because of their beliefs, aren't we basically saying that some people's religious views are more important than the law everyone else has to follow? It feels like it inevitably leads to a breakdown of equality under the law.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
