      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This is a valid concern, as making exemptions based on subjective interpretations of religious beliefs can create unequal treatment and create suspicion about others' faith. A moreroute approach would be to rely on established constitutional and statutory protections, such as the Freedom of Religion Act or the Religious Freedom Restoration Act, which provide broader safeguards against government overreach, rather than relying on ongoing case-by-case assessments.",
      "source": "target",
